First Congregational Church of Boylston
June 18 at 1:50 PM ·

The Boylston community has been so generous at providing foodstuffs and cash donations since the pandemic hit. Our food pantry is currently experiencing a large surplus of food and Stop & Shop gift cards beyond what we need to service our usual friends. You can help us serve new friends by using the attached form to make us aware of people you know who are in need. We are especially thinking of people who are unemployed, laid off, disabled, on a fixed income, and the like. You can mail the attached form to us or just provide is with the information by email. We will be grateful for anything you can do to help.

Warmly,
Pastor Kohl & the SLT

post_text:
With the global coronavirus pandemic affecting the ability of businesses to stay open and people being able to work; we need your help more than ever! We could use donations of non perishable food like canned veggies & pasta, cereal, mac and cheese, pasta, sauce, snacks. We also could use bread and milk if possible. And if you find it, we will even accept toilet paper!

Donations can be dropped at Town Hall, First Congregational Church of Boylston or St. Mary of the Hills.

Emergencies can be called into 508-579-1725 or 508-868-2048.

Thank you in advance.

First Congregational Church of Boylston
March 16 at 10:14 AM ·

***IMPORTANT INFO. FOR THOSE IN NEED***
*There is a large group of people in Boylston who are available to pick up groceries/supplies and make deliveries to those who are not comfortable leaving their homes or need help with purchasing groceries, medicine or household supplies. If you are a senior citizen, immunocompromised, in financial need, or not feeling well PLEASE don't hesitate to reach out if you need anything!!
*To put in a help request, please call the Boylston First Congregational Church office at (508) 869-2027 on Monday-Friday from 9-12.
*On week-ends/evenings, please call or text 508-873-3750 or (508) 579-1725.
**Local churches and groups will be distributing this message via e-mail. Please pass this on to friends, family and neighbors who may need assistance and are not on social media.
***Food Pantry Emergency: Please call or text to 508-579-1725 or to 508-868-2048.
** If you would like to be added to the volunteer list or donate, please message Michele Simler via Facebook Thank you!

post_text:
If you have kids in need of breakfast and lunch this summer, simply text "FOOD" to 877877 and you'll receive a message with the closest location where they can get free summer meals.

***Theres no paperwork to fill out, no income requirement to meet. They just feed the kids. It’s really that simple. They serve kids 18 and under. As long as they can eat table food, they can eat with this program.

No Kid Hungry has access to information about tens of thousands of groups serving free meals nationwide as part of the the U.S. Department of Agriculture’s (USDA) Summer Food Service.

Side note, Worcester has free breakfast and lunches for kids in the summer all over the city! As well as all day summer programs for kids 7 and up at many different parks in the city.

post_text:
Our community is so, so generous in so many ways. Where to begin?
Thank you to the children of Boylston Elementary School for the overwhelming response to the school's holiday food drive. As you can see... they really pulled through for the food pantry.
Thank you to the parents for the contributions and for all those who volunteered to help during this drive. Without your generosity this couldn't have happened.
Thank you to the BES Staff who helped collect the food and even donated themselves!
Thank you to the BES Student Council for all of your hard work getting this started and counting all the donations. You should be very proud of yourselves for your hard work and your community couldn't be more proud!
A special thank you to Christine Bradford for initiating this drive and for all your hard work getting it together and getting it delivered.
Generosity starts at home. It is taught through the school and a community like ours is one that other towns should strive to be like.
You just made the holidays a little brighter for some of our neighbors. Thank you!

Boylston Food Pantry
May 13, 2016 at 6:09 PM ·

The Boylston branch of the U.S. Post Office is having their annual food drive TOMORROW (Saturday, May 14th). You can donate by leaving food at your mailbox for when the Carrier delivers the mail, OR you can just drop it off at the Post Office on Route 140. We ask that you please consider donating! Thank you in advance!

*****Have your kids grab a bag together and make it FUN!!! Ask them to draw a picture with it for the Pantry and we can hang it up. With our new home in the Town Hall, the walls are bare and boring!

post_text: Did you know that the Food Bank is covered under the First Congregational Church of Boylston's 501c3 status and therefore any donations are tax deductible? All monetary donations can be made out to the "First Congregational Church of Boylston". Please just add "food pantry" to the memo line. Thank you!

post_text: If you know of a family that may be struggling, please let them know about the food bank. We do not take any financial information and try our best to make visiting the bank as confidential as possible. We have a reasonably private, separate entrance at the basement level of the municipal building. We are open Mondays 10AM-Noon & 6:30-7:45PM.
